<grammar><section><title>Articles</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;a/an&lt;/I&gt; with jobs.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_6_3_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>%undefined</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_6_3_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>I want to be &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; doctor.</text1a><text2>%undefined</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_6_3_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>I want to be &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;an&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; actor.</text2a><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;a/an&lt;/I&gt; if it's the first time you speak about something.  Use &lt;I&gt;the&lt;/I&gt; if you have already mentioned it or if there is only one.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_6_3_4.mp3</titlesound2><text3>I bought &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;a cake&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; today, and lots of fruit.</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_6_3_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>Was &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the cake&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; good?</text3a><text4>I met &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;a politician&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; today.</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_6_3_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>It wasn't &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the President&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;, was it?!</text4a></section><section><title>Articles</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;the&lt;/I&gt; with superlatives.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_6_3_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>He's a very nice boy.</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_6_3_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>He's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the nicest&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; boy in the school.</text1a><text2>She's very intelligent.</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_6_3_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>She's &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the most intelligent&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; person in the office.</text2a><sectiontitle2>We use no article when we make general statements with plural and uncountable nouns.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_6_3_10.mp3</titlesound2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_6_3_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Dogs&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; are wonderful pets.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_6_3_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Information&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; costs money.</text4a></section><section><title>Articles</title><sectiontitle>Use no article with most place names and names with South, East, West, North.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_6_3_13.mp3</titlesound><text1>%undefined</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_6_3_14.mp3</sound1><text1a>I live in &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;Germany&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text1a><text2>%undefined</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_6_3_15.mp3</sound2><text2a>He's from &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;South Africa&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text2a><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;the&lt;/I&gt; to say where in a country.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_6_3_16.mp3</titlesound2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_6_3_17.mp3</sound3><text3a>I live on &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the coast&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_6_3_18.mp3</sound4><text4a>She's from &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the north of England&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text4a></section><section><title>Articles</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;the&lt;/I&gt; for countries with State, Republic and Kingdom, and countries with plural names.</sectiontitle><titlesound>interm_Gram_6_3_19.mp3</titlesound><text1>%undefined</text1><sound1>interm_Gram_6_3_20.mp3</sound1><text1a>Wales is part of &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the United Kingdom&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text1a><text2>%undefined</text2><sound2>interm_Gram_6_3_21.mp3</sound2><text2a>I went to &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the West Indies&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text2a><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;the&lt;/I&gt; for rivers, seas, oceans and deserts.</sectiontitle2><titlesound2>interm_Gram_6_3_22.mp3</titlesound2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>interm_Gram_6_3_23.mp3</sound3><text3a>I swam in &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the Pacific Ocean&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>interm_Gram_6_3_24.mp3</sound4><text4a>She's never been to &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#3300cc'&gt;the Gobi Desert&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text4a></section></grammar>